gw.api.job

Interface IJobProcess

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IPolicyChangeProcess

    public interface IJobProcess
    Defines common methods of classes that handle process logic for jobs.

    • Method Detail

      • start

        void start()
        Method that starts this Job

      • initializeFuturePeriodJob

        void initializeFuturePeriodJob(Job futureJob)
        Initializes a newly created job for a future period based on this job, which is completing for an earlier period. This method is called by PolicyCenter when the new job is created, as part of promoting this job's period. The future job will already have its draft branch attached, with the CancellationDate and Canceled bit set correctly. The OOSJob bit on the job will also be set.
        Parameters:
        futureJob - The future job which is started in order to propagate changes from this job forward. The future job is guaranteed to be of the same type as this job.

      • expireJob

        void expireJob()
        Expires the entire Job:
        • Cancels all open activities
        • Expires all active PolicyPeriods on this Job
        • Completes the Job
        • Calls out to release remote lock on policy
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if this job is not open, or if any PolicyPeriod is on the main branch, or if Expire workflow trigger is not available for any PolicyPeriod, or if binding was requested on any PolicyPeriod, or if any PolicyPeriod is already bound.

      • canExpireJob

        boolean canExpireJob()
        True if the entire Job (i.e. all active periods on the job) can be expired by verifying the following conditions:
        • The job must be open
        • The "expireJob" trigger must be available for each period
        Returns:
        true if the job can be expired
